ht to 11:59 in the morning and p.m. to represent the last 12 hours of the day after noon to 11:59 at night. ; When using the 24-hour clock, we represent time by 4 digits, the first 2 digits from 00 to 23 represent the hour and the last 2 digits from 00 to 59 represent the minutes. For time from 1 p.m. to 11:59 p.m. , 12 is added to the time. For example, 1 pm = 1300 hours. '),(1011,'Time_Conversion','C',115,'1 hour = 60 minutes ; 1 minute = 60 seconds ; 1 day = 24 hours ; 1 week = 7 days ; 1 year = 12 months = 365 days'),(1012,'volume','C',115,'Volume is the amount of space occupied by a solid shape'),(1013,'Volume_Conversion','C',115,'1 Litre = 1000 ml = 1000 \\[cm^3\\]'),(1014,'Area_of_circle','F',115,'Area of circle = \\[\\pi\\]\\[\r^2\\]'),(1015,'Area_Of_Square','F',115,'Area of square = length x length'),(1016,'Area_Of_Triangle','F',115,'Area of triangle = \\[\\frac{1}{2}\\] x Base x Height'),(1017,'Circumference_of_circle','F',115,'Circumference of circle = 2\\[\\pi\\]r'),(1018,'Perimeter_Of_Square','F',115,'Perimeter of square = length x 4'),(1019,'speed','F',115,'Speed = \\[\\frac{distance}{time}\\]'),(1020,'Volume_of_cuboid','F',115,'Volume of cuboid = Length x breadth x height'),(1021,'angles_at_a_point','C',116,'Sum of angles that meet at a point = 360\\[\\circ\\]'),(1022,'Angles_on_a_straight_line','C',116,'Sum of angles on a straight line = 180\\[\\circ\\]'),(1023,'equilateral_triangle','C',116,'In an equilateral triangle, there are 3 equal sides and 3 equal angles, each of which is 60\\[\\circ\\]'),(1024,'isosceles_triangle','C',116,'In an isosceles triangle, there are 2 equal sides and the 2 angles opposite the equal sides are equal'),(1025,'net_of_solid','C',116,'A net of solid is a 2D figure that can be cut out and folded to form the solid. ; Each solid may have more than one net'),(1026,'parallel','C',116,'When two lines are parallel to each other, the distance between them are the same'),(1027,'parallelogram','C',116,'In a parallelogram: ; 1) Oppo